{"title":"Small piece of unrefined mithril","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Small_piece_of_unrefined_mithril","type":"markdown","data":"| \\*               |                                             |\n| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------- |\n| Name             | small piece of unrefined mithril            |\n| Appearance       | silvery metal stone                         |\n| Damage vs. small | 1d3                                         |\n| Damage vs. large | 1d3                                         |\n| To-hit bonus     | +0                                          |\n| Weapon skill     | [sling](/wiki/Sling \"Sling\")                |\n| Size             | [one-handed](/wiki/One-handed \"One-handed\") |\n| Base price       | 10000 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\")         |\n| Weight           | [1](/wiki/Weight \"Weight\")                  |\n| Material         | [mineral](/wiki/Mineral \"Mineral\")          |\n\nA **small piece of unrefined mithril** is a type of [stone](/wiki/Stone \"Stone\") that appears in [UnNetHack](/wiki/UnNetHack \"UnNetHack\"). It is made of [mineral](/wiki/Mineral \"Mineral\") rather than [mithril](/wiki/Mithril \"Mithril\"), and appears as a **silvery metal stone** when [unidentified](/wiki/Identification \"Identification\").\n\n## Generation\n\nSmall pieces of unrefined mithril are not randomly generated.\n\n2 to 16 small pieces of unrefined mithril are generated buried on the first level of the [Ruins of Moria](/wiki/Ruins_of_Moria \"Ruins of Moria\") branch.\n\n## Strategy\n\nThe main significance of small pieces of unrefined mithril is to be sold: its base price is more than twice that of a [dilithium crystal](/wiki/Dilithium_crystal \"Dilithium crystal\"). It cannot be used to [engrave](/wiki/Engrave \"Engrave\"), similar to a soft gem.\n\n[![This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.](/images/5/5d/Nh343var-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article describes a 3.4.3-based variant of NetHack. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Small piece of unrefined mithril - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Small_piece_of_unrefined_mithril\",\"wgTitle\":\"Small piece of unrefined mithril\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":157581,\"wgRevisionId\":157581,\"wgArticleId\":23634,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Variant-343 articles\",\"UnNetHack gems\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Small_piece_of_unrefined_mithril\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":23634,\"wgRequestId\":\"120bcb33dc75df327f2e7ae8\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEditorEnabledModules\":[],\"wgCategoryTreePageCategoryOptions\":\"{\\\"mode\\\":0,\\\"hideprefix\\\":20,\\\"showcount\\\":true,\\\"namespaces\\\":false}\"});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"user.styles\":\"ready\",\"user\":\"ready\",\"user.options\":\"rea